##################################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);
       
TEXT(beginproblem());

##################################
#  Setup

Context("Numeric");

$r = random(11,35,1);
$b = 1 + $r/100;
$decimal = $r/100;

$answer = Real("$b");


##################################
#  Main Text

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

What is the growth/decay factor per decade for a city whose population grows by $r$PERCENT per decade?
$BR
$BR
The growth/decay factor is $BITALIC b = $EITALIC 
\{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;


##################################
#  Answer Evaluation

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

ANS( $answer->cmp() );


##################################
#  Solution


BEGIN_SOLUTION
$BR
$BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 

The decennial growth factor (growth factor per 10 years) is 1 + $BITALIC r $EITALIC decade.  We have $BITALIC r $EITALIC = $r${PERCENT} = $decimal , so the growth factor $BITALIC b $EITALIC =  $b . 


END_SOLUTION


COMMENT('MathObject version');
ENDDOCUMENT();